[EXCERPT:windows]
1. Connect your DK2 headset to your computer, following the included Instruction Manual (which can also be found [online](http://static.oculus.com/sdk-downloads/documents/Oculus_Rift_DK2_Instruction_Manual.pdf)).
1. Run the **Oculus Configuration Utility** by:
	* **Right-clicking** on the Oculus icon in the system tray and selecting **Configuration Utility**, or
	* Opening the Start Menu and navigating to **Oculus Runtime > OculusConfigUtil**, or
	* Running `OculusConfigUtil.exe` found in `[InstallDirectory]/Tools/`.
1. Click on **Tools > Rift Display Mode**.

	![](RiftDisplayMode_menu.png)
1. Make sure the headset is in **Direct HMD Access from Apps** mode, then click **Apply** to save any changes. Close the window.
	
	![](DirectHMD.png)

[REGION:tip]
Your firmware version is listed in the Configuration Utility. If your version is not 2.12, complete the following steps to update the headset's firmware.
[/REGION]

1. Click on **Tools > Advanced > Update Firmware**.

	![](UpdateFirmware_menu.png)

	[REGION:note]
	Make sure Unreal Editor, Unreal Engine Launcher, and any other programs that might be using the Oculus are closed before you update the firmware. Otherwise, you will get a warning about closing other software and the firmware will not install.
	[/REGION]

1. Select `DK2Firmware_2_12.ovrf` when the file dialog appears, then click **Open**.

	![](Firmware.png)
1. The **Oculus Configuration Utility** will close. Reopen it by:
	* Opening the Start Menu and navigating to **Oculus Runtime > OculusConfigUtil**, or
	* Running `OculusConfigUtil.exe` found in `[InstallDirectory]/Tools/`.
1. Verify that the firmware is 2.12.
[/EXCERPT:windows]
